courses.subject: Major Ensemble
courses.customDesc:
Any Major Ensemble (100-level) course can go here.

Each Music major enrolled in at least 6 units of music courses must include a performance ensemble each quarter in order to qualify for applied study of voice or instruments. See current catalog for Major Ensemble at 100-level courses.

courses.subject: GE
courses.customDesc: One course from each of the following GE areas must be completed: A1, A2, A3, B1, B2, B4, Upper-Division B, C1, C2, Lower-Division C Elective, Upper-Division C, D1, D2, Upper-Division D, Lower-Division E, F, and GE Electives (8). Upper-Division B, Upper-Division C, and Upper-Division D should be taken only after Junior standing is reached (90 units). Refer to online catalog for GE course selection, United States Cultural Pluralism (USCP) and Graduation Writing Requirement (GWR). USCP requirement can be satisfied by some (but not all) courses within GE categories: Upper-Division B, C1, Upper-Division C, D1, Upper-Division D, or E.

courses.subject: Free Elective
